 {"id":"frankenredis-8xmq","title":"Downgrade FEATURE_PARITY.md replication status to honest assessment","description":"# Honest Replication Status\n\n## What\nChange FEATURE_PARITY.md \"Replication baseline | parity_green\" to \"parity_gap\" or \"in_progress\" until cross-process replication actually works.\n\n## Why\nThe current \"parity_green\" rating for replication is dishonest. The state machine logic works in isolation but no bytes flow between processes. Honesty about project status is a prerequisite for good engineering.\n\n## Implementation\n1. Update FEATURE_PARITY.md: change replication row status to \"in_progress\"\n2. Update notes to honestly describe what works (FSM logic, PSYNC decision math, offset tracking) and what does not (actual TCP replication)\n3. After replication epic is complete, upgrade back to parity_green with evidence\n\n## No Dependencies\nThis should be done immediately, before any replication implementation work.","status":"closed","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-07T03:11:17.272701785Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-07T18:52:37.119459043Z","closed_at":"2026-04-07T18:52:37.119284593Z","close_reason":"Updated FEATURE_PARITY.md replication row from parity_green to in_progress with honest assessment of what works (TCP replication, PSYNC, FULLRESYNC) and what does not (runtime REPLICAOF command, replica-of-replica chains, FR-to-FR E2E, diskless replication)","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
